				\begin{document}$$\triangle G=\triangle E+\triangle {E}_{{ZPE}}-T\triangle S-{neU}$$\end{document}where ΔE and ΔS are the changes in reaction energy and entropy, respectively; ΔEZPE is the difference in zero point energy between the adsorbed and gas phase molecules; U is the applied bias; and n is the electron transfer number involved in the reaction. U = 0 V for free energies was used in the diagrams demonstrated in this paper. For the frequency calculation, we considered the adsorbate *H, 2H*, and the Co atoms where intermediates are adsorbed. We calculated the ΔG for both the Volmer−Heyrovsky and Volmer−Tafel pathways. It was obtained that the rate-determining step (RDS) of Heyrovsky process possesses a lower reaction energy than that of Volmer-Tafel process (Supplementary Fig. 21). Therefore, the Volmer−Heyrovsky mechanism is the main pathway of HER in our system.
